==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Five
<hw>Five</hw> <pr>(f⟦imac⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>fif</ets>, <ets>five</ets>, AS. <ets>f⟦imac⟧f</ets>, <ets>f⟦imac⟧fe</ets>; akin to D. <ets>vijf</ets>, OS. <ets>f⟦imac⟧f</ets>, OHG. <ets>finf</ets>, <ets>funf</ets>, G. <ets>f⟦uum⟧nf</ets>, Icel. <ets>fimm</ets>, Sw. & Sw. Dan. <ets>fem</ets>, Goth. <ets>fimf</ets>, Lith. <ets>penki</ets>, W. <ets>pump</ets>, OIr. <ets>c⟦oacute⟧ic</ets>, L. <ets>quinque</ets>, Gr. <grk>pe`nte</grk>, ⟦AE⟧ol. <grk>pe`mpe</grk>, Skr. <ets>pa⟦ntil⟧can</ets>. ⟦root⟧303.  Cf. <er>Fifth</er>, <er>Cinque</er>, <er>Pentagon</er>, <er>Punch</er> the drink, <er>Quinary</er>.]</ety> <def>Four and one added; one more than four.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 565 --></p>

<p><cs><col><b>Five nations</b></col> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>, <cd>a
confederacy of the Huron-Iroquois Indians, consisting of five tribes:
Mohawks, Onondagas, Cayugas, Oneidas, and Senecas. They inhabited the
region which is now the State of new York.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Five</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Five
<hw>Five</hw> <pr>(f⟦imac⟧v)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
number next greater than four, and less than six; five units or
objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Five</qex> of them were wise, and <qex>five</qex> were
foolish.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. xxv. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A symbol representing this number, as 5, or
V.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Five-finger</ent>⟦br⟧
